description: Bengaluru in southern India is witnessing an unusually hot February and March, and in the last few years, it has received little rainfall in part due to human-caused climate change.
title: India's Bengaluru is fast running out of water, and a long, scorching summer still looms

description: Carlos Alcaraz defeated Jannik Sinner 1-6, 6-3, 6-2 to end the Italian’s 19-match winning streak and advance to the BNP Paribas Open final.
title: Alcaraz rallies from set down after 3-hour rain delay to end Sinner's winning streak at Indian Wells

description: Emani Jefferson scored 20 points with eight rebounds and five assists to help power Florida Gulf Coast to a 76-47 win over Central Arkansas in the Atlantic Sun Conference championship game.
title: Florida Gulf Coast tops Central Arkansas 76-47 to win seventh-straight ASUN title

description: Santiago Rodríguez scored for the second consecutive game, Kevin O’Toole added his first career MLS goal and New York City beat Toronto 2-1 for its first points of the season.
title: Rodríguez and O'Toole help NYCFC earn first points of season, beat Toronto 2-1

description: The performance of Damian McKenzie for the Chiefs against the Fijian Drua again has highlighted the high quality of flyhalves in Super Rugby Pacific this season.
title: Flyhalves shine in Super Rugby, chasing All Blacks, Wallabies spots

description: Pascal Siakam had 28 points and 11 rebounds, Aaron Nesmith scored 16 points and the Indiana Pacers beat the Brooklyn Nets 121-100 on Saturday night.
title: Pacers roll after halftime, beat the Nets 121-100

description: Alex Nylander scored twice and added an assist, Daniil Tarasov stopped 39 shots, and the Columbus Blue Jackets snapped a three-game losing streak with a 4-2 win over the San Jose Sharks.
title: Nylander scores twice, Tarasov stops 39 shots and Blue Jackets top Sharks 4-2

description: Cucho Hernández had a first-half goal and a second-half assist and the defending champion Columbus Crew cooled off the New York Red Bulls with a 3-0 victory on Saturday night.
title: Hernández sparks Crew to 3-0 victory over Red Bulls

description: Hannah Brandt and Hilary Knight each scored shootout goals and Aerin Frankel saved four of the five shots she faced as Boston beat Ottawa in a shootout, 2-1 in Detroit and in front of the largest crowd to watch a professional women’s hockey game in the United States.
title: Boston tops Ottawa 2-1 in shootout in front of largest U.S. crowd to watch a pro women's game

description: Morgan Morrison scored 14 points and grabbed nine rebounds, Belle Pellecchia added 12 points and NYU beat Smith 51-41 to win the program’s second NCAA Division III national championship and first since 1997.
title: Morgan Morrison, NYU women beat Smith 51-41 to win program's 2nd NCAA D-III title

description: Tyrese Maxey shook off a bloody nose caused by Brandon Miller’s flagrant foul to score 30 points, Kelly Oubre Jr. chipped in 22 and the Phladelphia 76ers withstood a fourth-quarter charge to beat the Charlotte Hornets 109-98 on Saturday night.
title: Maxey shakes off bloody nose from flagrant foul, leads 76ers over Hornets, 109-98

description: CJ McCollum scored 30 points, Zion Williamson had 26 points and 10 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 126-107 for their sixth victory in seven games.
title: McCollum's 30 points, Williamson's double-double propel the Pelicans past Trail Blazers 126-107

description: The Seattle Seahawks solidified a revamped linebacker unit signing former Miami inside linebacker Jerome Baker to a one-year contract.
title: Seahawks sign Jerome Baker to complete revamped group of linebackers

description: The Dallas Stars unveiled a statue of Hockey Hall of Famer Mike Modano during their home game against the Los Angeles Kings.
title: Dallas Stars unveil statue of Hockey Hall of Famer Mike Modano

description: Jaelen House had 28 points, Jamal Mashburn Jr. scored 21 and JT Toppin posted a double-double to propel sixth-seeded New Mexico to a 68-61 victory over No. 5 seed San Diego State in the championship game of the Mountain West Conference Tournament at the Thomas & Mack Center, earning the Lobos an aut
title: New Mexico fends off San Diego State 68-61 for MWC title, automatic berth in NCAA Tournament

description: Steven Stamkos scored two goals, Andrei Vasilevskiy stopped 47 shots and the Tampa Bay Lightning beat the Florida Panthers 5-3.
title: Steven Stamkos scores 2, Vasilevskiy has 47 saves as Lightning beat Panthers 5-3

description: Joel Embiid has been re-evaluated by doctors and they are “happy with the progress” the 76ers center is making following meniscus surgery on his left knee, Philadelphia head coach Nick Nurse said Saturday.
title: Embiid update: 76ers coach Nick Nurse says doctors are 'happy with the progress' following surgery

description: Led by Hysier Miller's 21 points, the No. 11 seed Temple Owls defeated the second-seeded Florida Atlantic Owls 74-73 in the American Athletic Conference Tournament.
title: Temple defeats Florida Atlantic 74-73 in American Athletic Conference Tournament

description: Donovan Clingan had 22 points and a career-best 16 rebounds, Jaylin Stewart gave No. 2 UConn an unexpected boost with three second-half 3-pointers during a decisive surge and the Huskies beat No. 10 Marquette 73-57 to win the Big East Tournament championship.
title: No. 2 UConn beats No. 10 Marquette 73-57 to win 1st Big East Tournament title since 2011

description: Deja Lee scored 21 points, Moulayna Johnson Sidi Baba added 13 points and nine rebounds, and UC Irvine defeated UC Davis 53-39 to win the Big West Conference Tournament.
title: UC Irvine women win Big West Championship, end long NCAA Tournament drought

description: The Los Angeles Chargers re-signed quarterback Easton Stick and added free agent defensive lineman Poona Ford.
title: Chargers re-sign quarterback Easton Stick and add defensive lineman Poona Ford

description: Niger’s junta says the U.S. military presence in the country is no longer justified after holding high-level talks with U.S. diplomatic and military officials this week, Niger plays a central role in the U.S. military’s operations in the Sahel, and is home to a major airbase.
title: Niger's junta says US military presence is no longer justified

description: Anastasiia Boldyreva scored 21 points, including eight in the closing minutes, and Middle Tennessee defeated Liberty 67-51 to win the Conference USA Tournament championship.
title: Boldyreva scores 21 and Middle Tennessee women win Conference USA, advance to NCAAs for 21st time

description: Milan Momcilovic had 18 points and Keshon Gilbert scored 16 as No. 7 Iowa State used a big second-half to rout No. 1 Houston 69-41 in the Big 12 Tournament final.
title: Blown away: No. 7 Iowa State blitzes No. 1 Houston in second half, wins Big 12 tourney title 69-41

description: Stephen Curry returned to the starting lineup on Saturday when the Golden State Warriors faced the Los Angeles Lakers.
title: Curry returns to Warriors' lineup going into pivotal Western Conference clash vs. Lakers

description: Syrian state media say Israeli airstrikes have hit several sites in southern Syria wounding a soldier.
title: Israel strikes several sites in Syria, wounding a soldier, Syrian military says

description: Kierra Wheeler scored 20 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, and top-seeded Norfolk State pulled away in the fourth quarter and beat second-seeded Howard 51-46 in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tournament championship.
title: Norfolk State women beat Howard 51-46 for MEAC title behind Wheeler's double-double

description: Cortez Garland scored 22 points and Nate Tucker scored 13 points and Trine University beat Hampden-Sydney 69-61 to claim the NCAA Division III national championship.
title: A Garland celebration as Trine tops No. 1-ranked Hampden-Sydney 69-61 in DIII championship

description: Andriana Avent scored 17 points and Jackson State defeated Alcorn State 68-44 on Saturday to cruise to their third Southwestern Athletic Conference title in four years and clinch an NCAA Tournament spot.
title: Avent scores 17 points and Jackson State women beat Alcorn State 68-44 to win SWAC Tournament title
